Approval ratings
The Gallup Poll tracks the approval ratings of US presidents according to a careful polling methodology
Each day they telephone \(n=1500\) adults and their sampling error for the approval ratings is about \(4\%\)
Let \(Y \sim \Bern(\mu)\), a Bernoulli (free throw shooting) distribution wth probability of success \(\mu\), \[
\Prob(Y =y) = \begin{cases} \mu, & y=1, \text{ (yes, approve)}\\
1-\mu, & y = 0, \text{ (no, do not approve)}
\end{cases}
\] If \(Y_1, \ldots, Y_n \IIDsim \Bern(\mu)\), then \[\begin{align*}
T &:= Y_1 + \cdots + Y_n \sim \Bin(n,\mu), \quad \Prob(T = y) = \binom{n}{y} \mu^y (1-\mu)^{n-y}\\
\barY &:= \frac 1n (Y_1 + \cdots + Y_n)
\appxsim  \Norm\bigl(\mu,\mu(1-\mu)/n\bigr) \quad \text{by the }\class{alert}{\text{Central Limit Theorem}}
\end{align*}\]
